&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;strong&gt;look after.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;The sentence indicates that she had to take care of the children in the absence of their parents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;The phrasal verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;look after&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to take care of or be responsible for someone or something, which fits the context of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;The other options &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;look out,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;look over,&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;look in&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; do not fit the context of taking care of children.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;Understanding the meaning of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;look after&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; in the context of the sentence helps to clarify that she was responsible for the children while their parents were away.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is- &lt;strong&gt;look after&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Look out (&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;सावधान रहना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means to be careful or vigilant.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Look over (&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;जांचना)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;means to quickly examine or review something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Look in (&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;झांकना)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;means to visit briefly or check on something or someone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;a complete change&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given idiom - &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;A sea change&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;a substantial change in perspective, especially one which affects a group or society at large on a particular issue.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We need &lt;strong&gt;a sea change&lt;/strong&gt; in our attitudes.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, we can conclude that the option which&amp;nbsp;best expresses the meaning of the idiom/phrase is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;a complete change&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer will be &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;A man of straw&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a person who is weak or lacks courage; someone who is easily influenced or overcome. (कमजोर या कायर व्यक्ति)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; In the face of adversity, he turned out to be &lt;strong&gt;a man of straw&lt;/strong&gt;, unable to take any strong decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;A weak or cowardly man&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to an individual who lacks strength or bravery. (कमजोर या कायर व्यक्ति)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He was considered&lt;strong&gt; a weak or cowardly man&lt;/strong&gt; because he always avoided confrontations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. A weak or cowardly man.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A man of character&lt;/strong&gt; (चरित्रवान व्यक्ति): A person who has strong moral and ethical principles.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He is known as a man of character, always standing up for what is right.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A man with no means&lt;/strong&gt; (साधनहीन व्यक्ति): A person who does not have financial resources or wealth.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Despite being a man with no means, he managed to make a name for himself through hard work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A generous man&lt;/strong&gt; (उदार व्यक्ति): A person who is willing to give more of something, especially money, than is usual or expected.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He is a generous man who always donates to charity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Pedagogy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Pedagogy:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;the method and practice of teaching, especially as an academic subject or theoretical concept&amp;nbsp;(शिक्षा शास्त्र).&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Some of the presentations, a few too many for comfort, lapsed into the familiar contortions of modern &lt;strong&gt;pedagogy&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above explanation, it can be concluded that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Pedagogy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;the correct word to substitute for the given description.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct choice is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s refer to all the other given options:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methodology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;a system of methods used in a particular area of study or activity (अध्ययन या गतिविधि के किसी विशेष क्षेत्र में उपयोग की जाने वाली विधियों की एक प्रणाली)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nascent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(especially of a process or organization) just coming into existence and beginning to display signs of future potential (विशेषकर किसी प्रक्रिया या संगठन का) बस अस्तित्व में आना और भविष्य की संभावनाओं के संकेत दिखाना शुरू करना&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flagship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the finest, largest, or most important one of a group of things (चीजों के समूह में सबसे बेहतरीन, सबसे बड़ा या सबसे महत्वपूर्ण)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e. &lt;strong&gt;Urban&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-200a6302-7fff-c1cf-2632-b5faa3c35d0b&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 40px; height: 35px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;35&quot; src=&quot;https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/28i2H4qZUMqoricKhH6aaLqxFoqVxqpmaJpMBy62DoGJbWBmmYJxPuBF6Wq_gGqfYCkpEpr0WIm9NnvtUCdNGqm-1_wqVyF46346wBwUiFK7AiZX8LxkL7abs3B0GOqVQ9Wwde-d&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Explanation&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Bucolic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means relating to or typical of rural life.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;country, pastoral, rural, rustic (also rustical)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;urban,&amp;nbsp;metro, metropolitan, municipal, nonagricultural, nonfarm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonym&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bucolic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Urbane&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is its&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;urban&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;of, relating to, characteristic of, or constituting a city.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence&lt;/span&gt;, we can say that &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;urban&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is nearly opposite in meaning to the given word.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meaning of other given options-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;tr style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;WORDS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;MEANING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Reserved&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;kept or set apart or aside for future or special use&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Rustic&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;relating to the countryside; rural&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Cheerful&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;full of good spirits&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/tbody&gt;
	&lt;/table&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-0bf84d85-7fff-12f0-36a4-d911daaa7bdd&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 120px; height: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;40&quot; src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/sWn1oC6mlNsROP-zVXMvAlT_Fqes0HlQMQeDtmr94LuJqLv7dOdQtJ2Q7iQ1JS5REaHqKFCFChrBmdKT4svOFMwg4y1JdWWC5pg4X0ls_aEdE-_EV4rBZGTOua1aQGpEgOl5QU9H&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;120&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Bucolic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is derived from the Latin &amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;bucolicus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot;, from Greek &amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;boukolikos&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot;, from &amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;boukolos&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot; cowherd, from &amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;bous&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot; &lt;strong&gt;head of cattle + -kolos (akin to Latin colere to cultivate)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Its&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first known use&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was in 1609.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Examples&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bucolic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sentence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;But across this &lt;strong&gt;bucolic&lt;/strong&gt; countryside, trouble is brewing&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;Water from a &lt;strong&gt;bucolic&lt;/strong&gt; pond drains into a sluice gate and rushes down a shallow millrace&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exacerbation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Revival&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;an improvement in the condition, strength, or fortunes and popularity of someone or something&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;question&quot;&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;An &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;economic&quot;&gt;economic&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;revival &lt;/strong&gt;was &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;sweeping&quot;&gt;sweeping&lt;/span&gt; the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;country&quot;&gt;country&lt;/span&gt; after the 2008 recession.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Marked Option &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Exacerbation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; refers to &lt;strong&gt;the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;process&quot;&gt;process&lt;/span&gt; of making something that is already &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;bad&quot;&gt;bad&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;even&quot;&gt;even&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;worse&quot;&gt;worse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;There is some &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;concern&quot;&gt;concern&lt;/span&gt; about the &lt;strong&gt;exacerbation &lt;/strong&gt;of &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;global&quot;&gt;global&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;warming&quot;&gt;warming&lt;/span&gt; by &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;animal&quot;&gt;animal&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;agriculture&quot;&gt;agriculture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;So, we can see that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Exacerbation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; can function as the opposite word of&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rev&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ival&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39; in meaning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amelioration&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;rArr; the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;process&quot;&gt;process&lt;/span&gt; of making a &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;bad&quot;&gt;bad&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;unpleasant&quot;&gt;unpleasant&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;situation&quot;&gt;situation&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;better&quot;&gt;better&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improvement &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; an &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;occasion&quot;&gt;occasion&lt;/span&gt; when something gets &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;better&quot;&gt;better&lt;/span&gt; or when one makes it &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;better&quot;&gt;better&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Restoration &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;act&quot;&gt;act&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;process&quot;&gt;process&lt;/span&gt; of &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;returning&quot;&gt;returning&lt;/span&gt; something to &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;its&quot;&gt;its&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;earlier&quot;&gt;earlier&lt;/span&gt; good &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;condition&quot;&gt;condition&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;position&quot;&gt;position&lt;/span&gt;, or to &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;its&quot;&gt;its&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;owner&quot;&gt;owner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Cling&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;means to hold on tightly to something or someone, especially emotionally or mentally.(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;चिपकना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;cling to the hope&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is idiomatic and commonly used to express holding onto a belief or expectation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Example: Despite the odds, she clung to the hope that her lost dog would return home.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;cling.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/u&gt; &amp;#39;I&lt;strong&gt; &lt;u&gt;cling&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to the hope that he&amp;#39;s still alive.&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: &amp;quot;hold&amp;quot; (पकड़) -&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;hold&amp;quot; can also convey the idea of maintaining a belief or expectation, it is not as specific or idiomatic in this context as &amp;quot;cling.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3: &amp;quot;take&amp;quot; (लेना) - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;Take&amp;quot; does not convey the idea of holding onto a belief or expectation in the same way as &amp;quot;cling.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: &amp;quot;grab&amp;quot; (पकड़) &lt;/strong&gt;- &amp;quot;Grab&amp;quot; means to seize or grasp something quickly and forcefully, which is not the intended meaning in this context of holding onto hope.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Behind the times&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to be old-fashioned or not aware of or using the latest ideas or techniques. (पुराने जमाने का या पुराने विचारों वाला)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;My grandfather is a bit&lt;strong&gt; behind the times;&lt;/strong&gt; he still listens to music on a cassette player.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt; i.e.&lt;strong&gt; To be old-fashioned.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: To go crazy&lt;/strong&gt; (पागल हो जाना): To lose one&amp;#39;s mind or behave in an irrational manner.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He went crazy after losing his job and started behaving erratically.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3: To become worse&lt;/strong&gt; (बिगड़ जाना): To deteriorate in condition or quality.
	&lt;ul&gt;
