		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;​Example: He&amp;#39;s a bit of a dilettante as far as technology is concerned.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above explanation, it is clear that the given sentence can be replaced by the word &amp;quot;regalia.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is option 2.&lt;/p&gt;

